Soul singer Timi Dakolo has argued any attempt to fool the present generation will be a hardball. Dakolo was addressing politicians on the current reality ahead of electioneering activities for 2023.   Wife to donate kidney to Eedris Abdulkareem     ‘Peter Obi can only win on Twitter’     Mixed reactions over PSquare’s comeback songs   The “Great Nation” singer said it is not just hard to fool the current generation but almost impossible. He noted this is so because this present generation consists of a vast majority of knowledgeable individuals who would resist political foolery. “Dear politicians, Fooling this generation is a very hard task. I mean Almost impossible. We are aware and knowledgeable,” he tweeted.